# **Operation Claymore: The 1941 British-Norwegian Raid on the Lofoten Islands**

## **Part of the [North West Europe Campaign](/North_West_Europe_Campaign)**

**Commandos watching fish oil tanks burning.**

**Date:** 4 March 1941 (1941-03-04)
**Location:** [Lofoten Islands](/Lofoten_Islands), Norway
**Coordinates:** 68°09′09″N 14°12′00″E
**Result:** British-Norwegian victory

### **Belligerents**
- **[United Kingdom](/United_Kingdom)**
- **[Norway](/Norway)**

**vs.**

- **[Germany](/Nazi_Germany)**
  - **[Quisling regime](/Quisling_regime)**

### **Commanders and Leaders**
- **[Louis K. Hamilton](/Louis_K._Hamilton)**
- **Clifford Caslon**
- **Joseph C. Haydon**
- **[Martin Linge](/Martin_Linge)**
- **[Lord Lovat](/Simon_Fraser,_15th_Lord_Lovat)**
- **Unknown German commanders**

### **Strength**
- **British & Norwegian Forces:**
  - 500 British commandos
  - 52 Norwegian volunteers
  - 7 ships (including infantry landing ships and destroyers)
- **German Forces:**
  - 1 [armed trawler](/Naval_trawler) (*Krebs*)
  - Small garrison forces

### **Casualties and Losses**
- **British & Norwegian:**
  - 1 wounded
- **German:**
  - 228 captured
  - 10 ships sunk

